 due to a decrease in cellular proliferation and an increase in apoptosis leading to a decrease in tissue outgrowth and the failure of the facial processes to meet and fuse (Lipinski, Song et al. 2010, Heyne, Melberg et al. 2015). This increase is apoptosis is believed to be due to a decrease in GLI1/2 target gene expression.&nbsp;&nbsp;", "timestamp": "Mon Jun 08 15:50:34 +0000 2026"}